<p style="margin:0;font-size:1rem;"><strong>What is an ARD meeting in Texas?</strong><br/>
  An ARD (Admission, Review, and Dismissal) meeting is the IEP meeting required by Texas law where the school and parents together review a child's special education eligibility and services. Parents must receive written notice at least <strong>5 calendar days</strong> before the meeting and may request a <strong>10-day recess</strong> at any time to seek advice.</p>
